# LGLC Website Templates - Cursor Rules

**This is the consolidated AI/IDE rules file for this project.** All AI coding assistants should reference this file.

This project uses a token-based design system for the Lesbian and Gay Liberation in Canada (LGLC) website templates.

**IMPORTANT:** This project follows the official **LGLC Brand Standards Manual** (`media/style_guide.pdf`).

## Core Principles

1. **Follow brand standards** - Use exact colors, typography, and design elements from the official brand manual
2. **Always use design tokens** - Never hardcode CSS values. All styling must use tokens from `css/design-tokens.css`
3. **Mobile-first responsive design** - Design for mobile first, enhance for larger screens
4. **Accessibility first** - Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible and meet WCAG 2.1 standards
5. **Semantic HTML** - Use proper HTML5 elements and ARIA attributes
6. **Component isolation** - Each component in its own CSS file

