### Link Color System (Context-Aware)

**IMPORTANT:** Links use a context-aware color system for better brand harmony and accessibility.

**Default Links (on white/light backgrounds):**
- Link: Brightened Navy (`#2D5A8C`)
- Hover: Navy (`#1C3664`)
- Use: `var(--text-link)` and `var(--text-link-hover)`

**Links on Colored Backgrounds:**
- **Red backgrounds:** White (stays white on hover, background changes to Red 80%)
- **Navy backgrounds:** White (stays white on hover)
- **Black backgrounds:** White (stays white on hover)
- **Yellow backgrounds:** Navy ‚Üí Black on hover
- **Grey backgrounds:** Navy ‚Üí Brightened Navy on hover

**Implementation:**
```css
/* Default - auto-applies to <a> tags on light backgrounds */
a { color: var(--text-link); }

/* Use context classes for colored backgrounds */
<div class="bg-red"><a href="#">White link</a></div>
<div class="bg-navy"><a href="#">White link</a></div>
<section class="team-section"><a href="#">Navy link on yellow</a></section>
```

**üìñ Full Documentation:** See `LINK-COLOR-SYSTEM.md` for complete specifications and usage examples.

