## CSS Rules

### Design Token Usage

**‚úÖ DO:**
- Always use design tokens via `var(--token-name)`
- Reference tokens from `css/design-tokens.css`
- Use semantic token names when available (`--text-primary` over `--color-primary-black`)

**‚ùå DON'T:**
- Never hardcode values (no `16px`, `#ED1C24`, `8px`, etc.)
- Never use raw `px` values for spacing, fonts, or sizes (except border widths which are already in tokens)
- Never define custom values in component CSS files

### CSS File Structure

1. **Import order is critical:**
   ```html
   <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/design-tokens.css">
   <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/your-component.css">
   ```

2. **Component files:**
   - Each component gets its own CSS file in `css/` directory
   - Import `design-tokens.css` first in HTML
   - Use design tokens exclusively

3. **Units:**
   - Use `rem` for all scalable values (spacing, fonts, sizes) via tokens
   - Use `px` ONLY for border widths (already defined in tokens)
   - Never mix units

### Example CSS:
```css
/* ‚úÖ Correct */
.my-component {
  padding: var(--spacing-4);
  color: var(--color-primary-red);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
}

/* ‚ùå Incorrect */
.my-component {
  padding: 16px;
  color: #ED1C24;
  border-radius: 8px;
  font-size: 18px;
}
```

## HTML Rules

### Semantic HTML
- Use semantic HTML5 elements: `<header>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, `<section>`
- Include ARIA labels where needed
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 ‚Üí h2 ‚Üí h3)

### Structure
- No inline styles - keep all CSS in stylesheets
- Import CSS in correct order (design-tokens.css first)
- Include `js/header.js` before closing `</body>` tag

## JavaScript Rules

### File Organization
- Component-specific JS in `js/` directory
- Keep JavaScript vanilla (no frameworks)
- Ensure accessibility features (keyboard navigation, ARIA updates)

### Accessibility
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Include focus management
- Provide screen reader announcements where needed

## Component Creation Guidelines

### When creating a new component:

1. **Create CSS file:**
   - New file in `css/` directory
   - Name it descriptively (e.g., `card.css`, `button.css`)

2. **Use design tokens:**
   - Reference existing tokens via `var(--token-name)`
   - If you need a new value, add it to `css/design-tokens.css` first
   - Never define custom values in component CSS

3. **Follow existing patterns:**
   - Look at `css/header.css` and `css/footer.css` for examples
   - Maintain consistency with existing components

